## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- **Framework**: React.js 18.x
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS / Material-UI
- **State Management**: Redux / Context API
- **HTTP Client**: Axios
- **Build Tool**: Vite / Create React App
- **Package Manager**: npm / yarn

### Backend
- **Runtime**: Node.js 16+
- **Framework**: Express.js
- **Database**: MongoDB
- **Authentication**: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
- **API Documentation**: Swagger/OpenAPI
- **Validation**: Joi / Zod
- **Environment**: dotenv

### DevOps & Deployment
- **Version Control**: Git
- **Repository**: GitHub
- **Frontend Hosting**: Vercel / Netlify
- **Backend Hosting**: Render / Railway / Heroku
- **Database Hosting**: MongoDB Atlas
- **Monitoring**: (if applicable)

### Additional Tools
- **API Testing**: Postman / Insomnia
- **Code Quality**: ESLint, Prettier
- **Task Runner**: npm scripts

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- **Node.js** (v16 or higher) - [Download](https://nodejs.org/)
- **npm** (v8 or higher) or **yarn**
- **Git** - [Download](https://git-scm.com/)
- **MongoDB** (local or Atlas account) - [Setup Guide](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/installation/)
- **Code Editor**: VS Code recommended

### Verify Installation

```bash
node --version
npm --version
git --version
```

## Installation

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/project-name.git
cd project-name
```

### 2. Install Backend Dependencies

```bash
cd backend
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

### 3. Install Frontend Dependencies

```bash
cd ../frontend
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

### 4. Verify Installation

```bash
npm list
```

## Configuration

### Backend Configuration

1. **Create `.env` file** in the `backend` directory:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

2. **Update the `.env` file** with your configuration (see [Environment Variables](#environment-variables))

### Frontend Configuration

1. **Create `.env` file** in the `frontend` directory:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

2. **Update with API base URL**:

```
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

## Usage

### Running Locally

#### Start Backend Server

```bash
cd backend
npm start
# or for development with hot reload
npm run dev
```

Backend will run on `http://localhost:5000`

#### Start Frontend Development Server

```bash
cd frontend
npm start
```

Frontend will run on `http://localhost:3000`

#### Access the Application

Open your browser and navigate to:
```
http://localhost:3000
```

### Build for Production

#### Build Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm run build
```

Output will be in `frontend/build` or `frontend/dist` directory.

#### Build Backend

```bash
cd backend
npm run build
```

## Project Structure

```
project-name/
├── backend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── config/          # Database and environment config
│   │   ├── controllers/     # Request handlers
│   │   ├── models/          # Database schemas (MongoDB)
│   │   ├── routes/          # API endpoints
│   │   ├── middleware/      # Custom middleware (auth, validation)
│   │   ├── services/        # Business logic
│   │   ├── utils/           # Utility functions
│   │   └── app.js           # Express app setup
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── server.js            # Entry point
│   └── package.json
│
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/      # Reusable React components
│   │   ├── pages/           # Page components
│   │   ├── services/        # API calls and external services
│   │   ├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
│   │   ├── context/         # Context API or Redux store
│   │   ├── utils/           # Utility functions
│   │   ├── styles/          # CSS/Tailwind styles
│   │   ├── App.jsx
│   │   └── main.jsx         # Entry point
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── index.html
│   └── package.json
│
├── docs/                    # Documentation
├── .gitignore
├── README.md
└── LICENSE
```

## API Documentation

### Base URL

```
http://localhost:5000/api
```

### Authentication

All protected endpoints require a JWT token in the Authorization header:

```
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>
```

### Endpoints Overview

#### User Management

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
|--------|----------|-------------|---|
| POST | `/auth/signup` | Register new user | No |
| POST | `/auth/login` | Login user | No |
| POST | `/auth/logout` | Logout user | Yes |
| GET | `/users/profile` | Get user profile | Yes |
| PUT | `/users/profile` | Update user profile | Yes |

#### Example Request

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"user@example.com","password":"password123"}'
```

### Response Format

**Success Response (200)**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Operation successful",
  "data": {}
}
```

**Error Response (4xx/5xx)**:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Error description",
  "error": "error_code"
}
```

### Complete API Documentation

For detailed API documentation with examples, visit:
- **Swagger UI**: `http://localhost:5000/api-docs` (if implemented)
- **Postman Collection**: See `docs/postman_collection.json`

## Database Schema

### User Model

```
User
├── _id (ObjectId)
├── firstName (String, required)
├── lastName (String)
├── email (String, required, unique)
├── password (String, hashed)
├── role (String: admin, user)
├── avatar (String, URL)
├── createdAt (Date)
└── updatedAt (Date)
```

### Entity Relationship Diagram

```
User (1) ---- (M) Post
User (1) ---- (M) Comment
Post (1) ---- (M) Comment
```

For detailed schema information, see `docs/database_schema.md`

## Environment Variables

### Backend `.env`

```
# Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/project_name
# or MongoDB Atlas
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/project_name

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_this
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# Email Configuration (if applicable)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_app_password

# Third-party APIs (if applicable)
CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_name
CLOUD_API_KEY=your_key
CLOUD_API_SECRET=your_secret
```

### Frontend `.env`

```
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
REACT_APP_ENV=development
```

**Important**: Never commit `.env` files to git. Use `.env.example` as a template.

## Deployment

### Deploy Frontend to Vercel

1. **Push to GitHub** (if not already done)

2. **Connect to Vercel**:
   - Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com)
   - Click "Import Project"
   - Select your GitHub repository

3. **Configure Environment Variables**:
   - Add `REACT_APP_API_URL` pointing to your backend

4. **Deploy**

### Deploy Backend to Render

1. **Create Render Account**: [render.com](https://render.com)

2. **Create New Web Service**:
   - Connect GitHub repository
   - Set build command: `npm install`
   - Set start command: `npm start`

3. **Add Environment Variables**:
   - Add all variables from `.env.example`
   - Importantly, set `MONGODB_URI` to your MongoDB Atlas connection string

4. **Deploy**

### Database Setup (MongoDB Atlas)

1. Create cluster at [mongodb.com/cloud](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas)
2. Create database user with strong password
3. Whitelist your IP addresses
4. Get connection string and add to backend `.env`

